# Employee Selection Decision Support System

## Overview

This project is a comprehensive, web-based Decision Support System (DSS) designed to assist Human Resources departments in objectively evaluating and selecting the best employees. The system implements two prominent Multi-Criteria Decision Making (MCDM) algorithms: Simple Additive Weighting (SAW) and Multi-Objective Optimization on the basis of Ratio Analysis (MOORA). 

By automating the evaluation process, the system eliminates subjective biases, handles complex multi-criteria data efficiently, and provides transparent, mathematically verifiable results.

## Key Features

- Complete CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for managing Criteria, Alternatives (Employees), and Performance Assessments.
- Automated calculation engine implementing both SAW and MOORA algorithms.
- Transparent and explainable computation: the system returns step-by-step mathematical details, including normalization matrices, weighted scores, and optimization results.
- Comparative analysis module to evaluate and compare the ranking consistency between the SAW and MOORA methods.
- Data import capabilities via Excel and automated report generation in PDF format.
- Robust, high-performance RESTful API built with FastAPI.
- Modern, responsive, and user-friendly frontend interface.

