## Security and Best Practices

- All API endpoints validate incoming data using Pydantic schemas to prevent malformed data injection.
- Database operations utilize SQLAlchemy ORM to prevent SQL injection vulnerabilities.
- Cascade delete rules are implemented at the ORM level to maintain referential integrity when criteria or alternatives are removed.
- The calculation engine includes strict validation to ensure mathematical operations (such as division) do not result in zero-division errors.

